section.section:
Of the 11 members of the Council:
one shall be the Secretary of Juvenile Services or a designee;
one shall be the Secretary of State Police or a designee;
one shall be the Secretary of Public Safety and Correctional Services or a designee;
one shall be the Executive Director of the Governor's Office of Crime Control and Prevention or a designee;
two shall be State's Attorneys who are recommended by the President of the Maryland State's Attorneys' Association, appointed by the Governor;
one shall be a sheriff, appointed by the Governor;
one shall represent the Maryland Chiefs of Police Association, appointed by the Governor;
one shall represent the Maryland Municipal Police Executives Association, appointed by the Governor; and
two shall represent the public, appointed by the Governor.
